'''Achref Abada''' ({{langx|ar|أشرف عبادة}}; born 15 June 1999) is an Algerian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|Center back]] for [[USM Alger]] in the [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1]] and the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://lfp.dz/en/player/41177 |title= Achref ABADA |website=lfp.dz |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/football-en-algerie/aso-chlef-achref-abada-le-defenseur-qui-monte-video-276317.html |title=ASO Chlef : Achref Abada, le défenseur qui monte (vidéo) |website=dzfoot.com |date=4 March 2025 |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
===ASO Chlef===
On 26 September 2021, Abada joined [[ASO Chlef]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://90dakika.dz/%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D9%84%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B9-%D8%A3%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%81-%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%85%D8%B6%D9%8A-%D8%AB/ |title=أولمبي الشلف-المدافع أشرف عبادة يمضي ثلاث مواسم |website=90dakika.dz |date=27 September 2021 |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/110477437536041/photos/a.128222742428177/338436271406822/ |title=المدافع المحوري ( متعدد المناصب ) " أشـرف عــبــادة " ، سادس المستقدمين في صفوف النادي |website=ASO Chlef |date=26 September 2021 |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref> Coach [[Sead Ramović]] saw him as the player who could immediately strengthen [[CR Belouizdad]]’s defense. Still under contract for one more season, Abada joined the club because of his current team’s financial situation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.competition.dz/actualites/ligue-1/crb-ramovic-veut-abada-pour-muscler-sa-defense.html |title=CRB : Ramovic veut Abada pour muscler sa défense |website=Competition |date=21 August 2025 |access-date=6 February 2026}}</ref>

===USM Alger===
On 31 January 2026, Achref Abada officially joined [[USM Alger]] on a contract lasting three and a half seasons, from [[ASO Chlef]]. With this signing, the Soustara based club strengthened its defensive line by recruiting a 26-year-old player, regarded as one of the promising defenders in his position. Abada notably distinguished himself during the [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]], held in Qatar, where he delivered several solid performances.<ref name="transferts-abada-sengage-officiellement-avec-lusma">{{cite web |url=https://www.competition.dz/actualites/ligue-1/transferts-abada-sengage-officiellement-avec-lusma.html |title=Transferts : Abada s’engage officiellement avec l’USMA |website=competition.dz |date=5 February 2026 |access-date=5 February 2026}}</ref><ref name="usm-alger-achraf-abada-sengage-pour-trois-ans-et-demi">{{cite web |url=https://mediafootdz.dz/usm-alger-achraf-abada-sengage-pour-trois-ans-et-demi/ |title=USM Alger : Achraf Abada s’engage pour trois ans et demi |website=mediafootdz.dz |date=6 February 2026 |access-date=6 February 2026}}</ref>

In a statement published on 5 February 2026 on its official social media platforms, USM Alger announced that the player had been officially registered and cleared by [[FIFA]], following the review of the administrative file submitted by the club. The Red and Black management further specified that the player’s registration on FIFA’s electronic platform was completed on 31 January 2026 at 00:05, ensuring full compliance with all administrative and legal procedures related to the transfer.<ref name="transferts-abada-sengage-officiellement-avec-lusma" /><ref name="usm-alger-achraf-abada-sengage-pour-trois-ans-et-demi" />

The transfer is reportedly the most expensive in Algerian football history, valued at 100 million dinars. [[USM Alger]] paid 8 billion centimes immediately, with 2 billion centimes due at the end of the season. Abada also receives a monthly salary of 410 million centimes. [[ASO Chlef]] secured a clause granting 30% of any future transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://lagazettedufennec.com/mercato-usma-achraf-abada-les-chiffres-qui-donnent-le-vertige/ |title=Mercato / USMA : Achref Abada, les chiffres qui donnent le vertige |website=La gazette du fennec |date=6 February 2026 |access-date=7 February 2026}}</ref> The deal also includes a special clause: USM Alger will finance ASO Chlef’s summer training camp next year if Abada is selected for the national team to prepare for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://lalgerieaujourdhui.dz/abada-le-transfert-record-de-la-ligue-1/ |title=Abada, le transfert record de la Ligue 1 ! |website=L'Algerie Aujourdhui |date=7 February 2026 |access-date=7 February 2026}}</ref>

Achraf Abada was unable to participate in the [[2025–26 CAF Confederation Cup]] with USM Alger due to an administrative issue related to his registration on the CAF player list, despite being signed during the winter transfer window.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/football-en-algerie/usma-abada-et-azzi-non-qualifies-en-coupe-dafrique-290045.html |title=USMA : Abada et Azzi non-qualifiés en coupe d'Afrique ! |website=DZ Foot |date=15 February 2026 |access-date=7 March 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Abada was called for [[2024 African Nations Championship]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cafonline.com/fr/championnat-dafrique-des-nations/news/bougherra-devoile-la-liste-definitive-de-lalgerie-pour-le-chan/ |title=Bougherra dévoile la liste définitive de l'Algérie pour le CHAN |website=cafonline.com |date=23 July 2025 |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref> and [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/equipes-nationales/en-a-la-liste-des-23-de-bougherra-pour-la-coupe-arabe-286870.html |title=EN A' : La liste des 23 de Bougherra pour la Coupe Arabe ! |website=dzfoot.com |date=23 November 2025 |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref>

